I can confirm that I see this behavior in R-devel

```
R Under development (unstable) (2026-04-10 r89864) -- "Unsuffered Consequences"
Copyright (C) 2026 The R Foundation for Statistical Computing
Platform: aarch64-apple-darwin23.5.0

&lt;snip&gt;

&gt; `list_sub&lt;-` = function(expr, idx, env = parent.frame(), value)
+ {
+     expr = eval(substitute(expr), env)
+     expr[[idx]] = value;
+     return (expr)
+ }
&gt; test = list(a = 1)
&gt; 
&gt; list_sub(test, "b") = 1 #1
&gt; list_sub(test, "b") &lt;- 1
&gt; for (anything in 1) {
+     list_sub(test, "b") = 1 #2
+ }
Error in eval(substitute(expr), env) : object '*tmp*' not found
&gt; list_sub(test, "b") &lt;- 1
&gt; `list_sub&lt;-`
function(expr, idx, env = parent.frame(), value)
{
    expr = eval(substitute(expr), env)
    expr[[idx]] = value;
    return (expr)
}
&lt;bytecode: 0x136503ba0&gt;
```

Furthermore as we see above it isn't actually a consequence of calling the
function after it is compiled, but rather seems to be from calling it within
the loop that does it.

